I have watched film âMiss Americanaâ recently. Itâs about american singer and songwriter Taylor Swift. Sheâs famous all around the world so she has impact on a lot of people. This is documentary film about biography of this woman. The movie describes how Taylor Swift uses her music to fight for rights for LGBTQ people. 

Taylor Swift had stayed non-political for years, but one day she found courage to speak out about what she really thinks. She published her opinion on social media before voting in the USA and made a huge contribution on that how many young people registered for voting. A few years later she placed a petition about LGBTQ society rights in the end of âYou need to calm downâ music video. The petition was signed by 500 thousand of people, which is four times more signs than it is needed to get a response from the White House.

I hadnât known, how hard and risky it was for her, before I watched the film. She exposed herself for a lot of hate. Many people such as her dad or her journalist dissuaded her of doing this. My class has attended a panel discussion on facilities which should receive money from our local authorities. We think that sport centres and public gardens are good investments and will make our town a better place.  

 

Sport centres are good for keeping ourselves healthy and strong, but pubic gardens are capable of delivering fresh and clean air due to many trees growing around the paths. We could spend this additional money to build public gyms and courts so that they will be free and open for everyone.  

 

Speaking of availability, public gardens are not private and everyone can access it without any costs. On the other hand, that can cause problem, because more and more people would rather not spend any money and stay healthy than paying for exclusive training. But in my opinion, that wonât be an issue thanks to additional space we could create with those funds. 

 

If we could make more public gardens, our city will be more attractive for people looking for a new place to live. Sports centres are not as environmentally friendly as gardens and with groth in public awareness of harm civilisation does, people would rather donate money to make our place more and more ecological.  

 

Unfortunately, we cannot make a clean, public swimming pool, because of weather conditions or social responsibility. Sport centres are the only option for pools. 

 

In summary, I think public gardens are a better option and not only they give us fresh air and space to rest, they also can be a great place to work out and train.
